BLF leader Andile Mngxitama says black people are tenants in South Africa. Courtesy #DStv403 PRETORIA - Black First Land First leader Andile Mngxitama has accused ANC, DA and the EFF of representing white monopoly capital. Mngxitama says the three parties belong to the "same individuals that own the economy and the land". He says there's one party in Parliament and that party will make sure there's no expropriation of land without compensation. READ: BLF ordered to remove 'Land or Death' slogan “There is only one party in parliament which is part of white monopoly capital. It may be ANC, DA or EFF but there is one party in parliament which is white monopoly capital and that party is going to make sure there is no expropriation of land without compensation,” he said. Mngxitama says black South Africans are still facing the same challenges faced by Steven Bantu Biko in the late 60s and 70s. "Black people are scared of themselves, black people are not yet where they should be in terms of psychological liberation," he said. READ: 2019 Election Results He says BLF is the only movement that represents the interest of black people. The BLF is among the 35 disgruntled political parties calling for an independent audit of the entire election process, and for the results to be acknowledged by the international community.